THE AGGREGATE MARKET VALUE OF COMMON STOCK HELD BY NON-AFFILIATES (BASED ON THE CLOSING PRICE ON THE LAST BUSINESS DAY OF THE REGISTRANTS MOST

RECENTLY COMPLETED SECOND FISCAL QUARTER AS REPORTED ON THE NEW YORK STOCK EXCHANGE-COMPOSITE TRANSACTIONS) WAS $53.7 BILLION. ALL EXECUTIVE OFFICERS AND DIRECTORS OF THE REGISTRANT AND ALL PERSONS FILING A SCHEDULE 13D WITH THE SECURITIES AND

EXCHANGE COMMISSION IN RESPECT TO REGISTRANTS COMMON STOCK HAVE BEEN DEEMED, SOLELY FOR THE PURPOSE OF THE FOREGOING CALCULATION, TO BE AFFILIATES OF THE REGISTRANT.

THERE WERE 1,851,027,161 SHARES OF COMMON STOCK OUTSTANDING AS OF NOVEMBER 14, 2008.

