DISTRIBUTION AND WORLDWIDE HOME ENTERTAINMENT, PARTIALLY OFFSET BY AN INCREASE IN MUSIC DISTRIBUTION.

LOWER COSTS IN WORLDWIDE THEATRICAL

DISTRIBUTION WERE PRIMARILY DUE TO LOWER DISTRIBUTION EXPENSES, PARTICIPATION COSTS AND FILM COST WRITE-DOWNS. LOWER DISTRIBUTION EXPENSES WERE DRIVEN BY A DECREASE IN INTERNATIONAL MARKETS AS FISCAL 2006 INCLUDED MORE HIGH PROFILE FILMS THAT HAD

EXTENSIVE MARKETING CAMPAIGNS. THE DECREASE IN PARTICIPATION COSTS WERE DRIVEN BY THE STRONG PERFORMANCE OF

