DISCLOSURES ABOUT DERIVATIVE INSTRUMENTS AND HEDGING

ACTIVITIES  AN AMENDMENT OF FASB STATEMENT NO. 133

(SFAS 161). SFAS 161 AMENDS AND EXPANDS THE DISCLOSURE REQUIREMENTS FOR DERIVATIVE INSTRUMENTS AND HEDGING ACTIVITIES BY REQUIRING ENHANCED DISCLOSURES ABOUT HOW AND WHY THE COMPANY

USES DERIVATIVE INSTRUMENTS, HOW DERIVATIVE INSTRUMENTS AND RELATED HEDGED ITEMS ARE ACCOUNTED FOR, AND HOW DERIVATIVE INSTRUMENTS AND RELATED HEDGED ITEMS AFFECT THE COMPANYS FINANCIAL POSITION, FINANCIAL PERFORMANCE AND CASH FLOWS. SFAS 161

IS EFFECTIVE FOR THE COMPANY IN THE SECOND QUARTER OF FISCAL YEAR 2009.

