PLAN CONTRIBUTIONS

DURING FISCAL 2008, THE COMPANY WAS NOT REQUIRED TO MAKE CONTRIBUTIONS TO ITS PENSION PLANS UNDER FUNDING REGULATIONS ASSOCIATED WITH

THE PENSION PROTECTION ACT OF 2006 (PPA) AND CONTRIBUTED $29 MILLION TO PENSION AND POSTRETIREMENT MEDICAL PLANS NOT SUBJECT TO PPA. THE COMPANY EXPECTS PENSION AND POSTRETIREMENT MEDICAL PLAN CONTRIBUTIONS IN FISCAL 2009 TO RANGE FROM $200 MILLION

TO $300 MILLION. FINAL FUNDING REQUIREMENTS FOR FISCAL 2009 WILL BE DETERMINED BASED ON OUR JANUARY 1, 2009 FUNDING ACTUARIAL VALUATION. THE COMPANY MAY ALSO MAKE DISCRETIONARY CONTRIBUTIONS ABOVE THE MINIMUM REQUIREMENTS.

